      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my fiddle leaf fig is looking a bit sad and the roots are starting to come out the bottom of the pot. how do i repot it without killing it? what kind of dirt should i get?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "First, gently loosen the roots at the bottom of the current pot and work your way up to remove about half the root ball, then carefully remove the plant from its container. For the new soil, choose a well-draining cactus or succulent mix rather than standard potting soil, as these plants typically come from arid regions and require excellent drainage to prevent root rot. Since they can be quite old, make sure the new pot is only slightly larger than the last one to avoid immediate root shock.",
