    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Healthy roots should be firm to the touch, whitish or light tan in color, and have a slightly sticky texture known as \"calluses\" where they connect. If the outer layer falls off easily, leaving behind soft, dark mush underneath, or if the roots smell foul before you plant them, they are likely rotting and need trimming. A quick cure is to gently pull everything off, discarding any black mushy sections until only firm, white roots remain before replanting.",
